President Biden will have a virtual meeting with Prime Minister Kishida Fumio of Japan on January 21. The purpose of the meeting is to strengthen the relationship between the two countries in various aspects, including government, economy, and people. The meeting will emphasize the importance of the U.S.-Japan Alliance in promoting peace, security, and stability in the Indo-Pacific region and worldwide. President Biden aims to collaborate with Prime Minister Kishida on advancing their shared vision of a free and open Indo-Pacific. They will also discuss important issues such as combating COVID-19, addressing the climate crisis, and partnering on new technologies, including through the Quad.